{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BAn7195Mr9XpkNK4tc2u3T","type":"tool_result","content":"<persisted-output>\nOutput too large (68.9KB). Full output saved to: /home/vscode/.claude/projects/-workspaces-rng-utopia/aa22a004-7967-4272-b3ce-42c86f057c37/tool-results/toolu_01BAn7195Mr9XpkNK4tc2u3T.json\n\nPreview (first 2KB):\n[\n  {\n    \"type\": \"text\",\n    \"text\": \"Perfect! I can see there are already test files. Let me now compile my findings for you:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Complete File Contents for FR-6 User Detail Testing\\n\\n### 1. Query Module: `get-peek-user-detail.ts`\\n\\n```typescript\\nimport type {\\n  PeekChallengeAssignmentSummary,\\n  PeekCrateDropRow,\\n  PeekFraudFlagRow,\\n  PeekGameEntryRow,\\n  PeekKolRate,\\n  PeekLinkedAccountRow,\\n  PeekPlayerPoints,\\n  PeekPointGrantRow,\\n  PeekReferralClaimRow,\\n  PeekReferralEarningsSummary,\\n  PeekTelegramLinkTokenRow,\\n  PeekTransactionRow,\\n  PeekUserAttentionFlags,\\n  PeekUserDetail,\\n  PeekUserQueueEventRow,\\n} from \\\"../../../lib/types/peek\\\";\\nimport { getSqlClient } from \\\"../client\\\";\\n\\nexport const PEEK_USER_DETAIL_RECENT_LIMIT = 25;\\nexport const PEEK_USER_DETAIL_TOKEN_LIMIT = 10;\\n\\ntype Sql = ReturnType<typeof getSqlClient>;\\n\\ntype GetPeekUserDetailOptions = {\\n  sql?: Sql;\\n  recentLimit?: number;\\n  tokenLimit?: number;\\n};\\n\\nexport function formatUserHeading(user: {\\n  userId: string;\\n  username: string | null;\\n}) {\\n  return user.username ?? user.userId;\\n}\\n\\nexport async function getPeekUserDetail(\\n  userId: string,\\n  options: GetPeekUserDetailOptions = {},\\n): Promise<PeekUserDetail | null> {\\n  const sql = options.sql ?? getSqlClient();\\n  const recentLimit = clampPositiveInt(\\n    options.recentLimit,\\n    PEEK_USER_DETAIL_RECENT_LIMIT,\\n  );\\n  const tokenLimit = clampPositiveInt(\\n    options.tokenLimit,\\n    PEEK_USER_DETAIL_TOKEN_LIMIT,\\n  );\\n\\n  // Identity + linked-account telegram view (preserved as queries[0] so the\\n  // 303-era listing/detail tests continue to assert the same SQL contract).\\n  const [user] = await sql<\\n    Array<{\\n      userId: string;\\n      username: string | null;\\n      wallet: string;\\n      joinedAt: string;\\n      avatarUrl: string | null;\\n      heatMultiplier: string;\\n      profilePointsBalance: string;\\n      referralCode: string | null;\\n      referrerUserId: string | null;\\n    \n...\n</persisted-output>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa22a004-7967-4272-b3ce-42c86f057c37","uuid":"73f5861c-ef51-498f-9de2-92aa267f9a5b","timestamp":"2026-04-25T12:03:06.927Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to write tests for the FR-6 expanded user detail in the peek app. Please report the contents of these files so I can see them in full:\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/db/queries/get-peek-user-detail.ts` — the query module to test\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/components/user-detail-view.tsx` — the component to test\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts` — type definitions (just the user-detail-related types)\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/audit/writer.ts` — the audit writer (so I know its signature)\n5. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/audit/__tests__/writer.test.ts` — existing test pattern using a SQL mock\n6. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/db/queries/__tests__/get-command-center-attention.test.ts` — existing query test pattern with SQL mock\n7. List files in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/db/queries/__tests__/` and `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/components/__tests__/`\n\nPlease dump the full content of files 1, 2, 4, 5, 6, plus the user-detail-related types from file 3. Reply with concrete file content; I will use this directly. Thorough.","agentId":"a04e03461144a5caa","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I can see there are already test files. Let me now compile my findings for you:\n\n---\n\n## Complete File Contents for FR-6 User Detail Testing\n\n### 1. Query Module: `get-peek-user-detail.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport type {\n  PeekChallengeAssignmentSummary,\n  PeekCrateDropRow,\n  PeekFraudFlagRow,\n  PeekGameEntryRow,\n  PeekKolRate,\n  PeekLinkedAccountRow,\n  PeekPlayerPoints,\n  PeekPointGrantRow,\n  PeekReferralClaimRow,\n  PeekReferralEarningsSummary,\n  PeekTelegramLinkTokenRow,\n  PeekTransactionRow,\n  PeekUserAttentionFlags,\n  PeekUserDetail,\n  PeekUserQueueEventRow,\n} from \"../../../lib/types/peek\";\nimport { getSqlClient } from \"../client\";\n\nexport const PEEK_USER_DETAIL_RECENT_LIMIT = 25;\nexport const PEEK_USER_DETAIL_TOKEN_LIMIT = 10;\n\ntype Sql = ReturnType<typeof getSqlClient>;\n\ntype GetPeekUserDetailOptions = {\n  sql?: Sql;\n  recentLimit?: number;\n  tokenLimit?: number;\n};\n\nexport function formatUserHeading(user: {\n  userId: string;\n  username: string | null;\n}) {\n  return user.username ?? user.userId;\n}\n\nexport async function getPeekUserDetail(\n  userId: string,\n  options: GetPeekUserDetailOptions = {},\n): Promise<PeekUserDetail | null> {\n  const sql = options.sql ?? getSqlClient();\n  const recentLimit = clampPositiveInt(\n    options.recentLimit,\n    PEEK_USER_DETAIL_RECENT_LIMIT,\n  );\n  const tokenLimit = clampPositiveInt(\n    options.tokenLimit,\n    PEEK_USER_DETAIL_TOKEN_LIMIT,\n  );\n\n  // Identity + linked-account telegram view (preserved as queries[0] so the\n  // 303-era listing/detail tests continue to assert the same SQL contract).\n  const [user] = await sql<\n    Array<{\n      userId: string;\n      username: string | null;\n      wallet: string;\n      joinedAt: string;\n      avatarUrl: string | null;\n      heatMultiplier: string;\n      profilePointsBalance: string;\n      referralCode: string | null;\n      referrerUserId: string | null;\n      referrerCode: string | null;\n      refereeCount: number;\n      telegramLinkState: \"active\" | \"none\";\n      linkedAt: string | null;\n      telegramUserId: string | null;\n      telegramUsername: string | null;\n    }>\n  >`\n    select\n      pp.user_id as \"userId\",\n      pp.username as \"username\",\n      pp.wallet as \"wallet\",\n      pp.created_at::text as \"joinedAt\",\n      pp.avatar_url as \"avatarUrl\",\n      pp.heat_multiplier::text as \"heatMultiplier\",\n      pp.points_balance::text as \"profilePointsBalance\",\n      rc.code as \"referralCode\",\n      rl.referrer_user_id as \"referrerUserId\",\n      ref_code.code as \"referrerCode\",\n      (\n        select count(*)::int\n        from referral_links outbound\n        where outbound.referrer_user_id = pp.user_id\n      ) as \"refereeCount\",\n      coalesce(tla.status, 'none') as \"telegramLinkState\",\n      rl.created_at::text as \"linkedAt\",\n      tla.telegram_user_id as \"telegramUserId\",\n      tla.telegram_username as \"telegramUsername\"\n    from player_profiles pp\n    left join referral_codes rc on rc.user_id = pp.user_id\n    left join referral_links rl on rl.referee_user_id = pp.user_id\n    left join referral_codes ref_code on ref_code.user_id = rl.referrer_user_id\n    left join lateral (\n      select\n        status,\n        provider_account_id as telegram_user_id,\n        nullif(metadata_json->>'telegramUsername', '') as telegram_username\n      from linked_accounts\n      where user_id = pp.user_id\n        and provider = 'telegram'\n        and status = 'active'\n      limit 1\n    ) tla on true\n    where pp.user_id = ${userId}\n  `;\n\n  if (!user) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  const wallet = user.wallet;\n\n  const [\n    outboundReferees,\n    linkedAccounts,\n    recentTelegramLinkTokens,\n    kolRate,\n    referralEarnings,\n    recentReferralClaims,\n    points,\n    recentPointGrants,\n    recentCrateDrops,\n    challengeSummary,\n    recentGameEntries,\n    recentTransactions,\n    fraudFlags,\n    recentUserQueueEvents,\n    selfReferralRow,\n  ] = await Promise.all([\n    fetchOutboundReferees(sql, userId),\n    fetchLinkedAccounts(sql, userId),\n    fetchRecentTelegramLinkTokens(sql, userId, tokenLimit),\n    fetchKolRate(sql, userId),\n    fetchReferralEarnings(sql, userId),\n    fetchRecentReferralClaims(sql, userId, recentLimit),\n    fetchPlayerPoints(sql, userId),\n    fetchRecentPointGrants(sql, userId, recentLimit),\n    fetchRecentCrateDrops(sql, userId, recentLimit),\n    fetchChallengeSummary(sql, userId),\n    fetchRecentGameEntries(sql, userId, recentLimit),\n    fetchRecentTransactions(sql, userId, recentLimit),\n    fetchFraudFlags(sql, userId, recentLimit),\n    fetchRecentUserQueueEvents(sql, userId, wallet, recentLimit),\n    fetchSelfReferralIndicator(sql, userId),\n  ]);\n\n  const attention = computeAttention({\n    recentReferralClaims,\n    recentUserQueueEvents,\n    fraudFlags,\n    recentCrateDrops,\n    selfReferralRow,\n  });\n\n  return {\n    user: {\n      userId: user.userId,\n      username: user.username,\n      wallet: user.wallet,\n      joinedAt: user.joinedAt,\n      referralCode: user.referralCode,\n      referrerUserId: user.referrerUserId,\n      referrerCode: user.referrerCode,\n      refereeCount: user.refereeCount,\n      telegramUsername: user.telegramUsername,\n      telegramUserId: user.telegramUserId,\n      avatarUrl: user.avatarUrl,\n      heatMultiplier: user.heatMultiplier,\n      profilePointsBalance: user.profilePointsBalance,\n    },\n    inboundReferral: {\n      referrerUserId: user.referrerUserId,\n      referrerCode: user.referrerCode,\n      linkedAt: user.linkedAt,\n    },\n    outboundReferees,\n    telegram: {\n      state: user.telegramLinkState,\n      telegramUserId: user.telegramUserId,\n      telegramUsername: user.telegramUsername,\n    },\n    linkedAccounts,\n    recentTelegramLinkTokens,\n    kolRate,\n    referralEarnings,\n    recentReferralClaims,\n    points,\n    recentPointGrants,\n    recentCrateDrops,\n    challengeSummary,\n    recentGameEntries,\n    recentTransactions,\n    fraudFlags,\n    recentUserQueueEvents,\n    attention,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction clampPositiveInt(value: number | undefined, fallback: number): number {\n  if (typeof value !== \"number\" || !Number.isFinite(value)) return fallback;\n  const floored = Math.floor(value);\n  if (floored <= 0) return 1;\n  return floored;\n}\n\nasync function fetchOutboundReferees(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n): Promise<PeekUserDetail[\"outboundReferees\"]> {\n  return sql<\n    Array<{\n      refereeUserId: string;\n      refereeUsername: string | null;\n      createdAt: string;\n    }>\n  >`\n    select\n      rl.referee_user_id as \"refereeUserId\",\n      pp.username as \"refereeUsername\",\n      rl.created_at::text as \"createdAt\"\n    from referral_links rl\n    left join player_profiles pp on pp.user_id = rl.referee_user_id\n    where rl.referrer_user_id = ${userId}\n    order by rl.created_at desc\n  `;\n}\n\nasync function fetchLinkedAccounts(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n): Promise<ReadonlyArray<PeekLinkedAccountRow>> {\n  return sql<Array<PeekLinkedAccountRow>>`\n    select\n      id::text as \"id\",\n      provider,\n      provider_account_id as \"providerAccountId\",\n      status,\n      nullif(metadata_json->>'telegramUsername', '') as \"telegramUsername\",\n      metadata_json as \"metadataJson\",\n      linked_at::text as \"linkedAt\",\n      updated_at::text as \"updatedAt\"\n    from linked_accounts\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n    order by linked_at desc\n  `;\n}\n\nasync function fetchRecentTelegramLinkTokens(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n  limit: number,\n): Promise<ReadonlyArray<PeekTelegramLinkTokenRow>> {\n  return sql<Array<PeekTelegramLinkTokenRow>>`\n    select\n      id::text as \"id\",\n      status,\n      telegram_user_id as \"telegramUserId\",\n      telegram_username as \"telegramUsername\",\n      expires_at::text as \"expiresAt\",\n      redeemed_at::text as \"redeemedAt\",\n      created_at::text as \"createdAt\"\n    from telegram_link_tokens\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n    order by created_at desc\n    limit ${limit}\n  `;\n}\n\nasync function fetchKolRate(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n): Promise<PeekKolRate | null> {\n  const [row] = await sql<\n    Array<{\n      rateBps: number;\n      setBy: string;\n      createdAt: string;\n      updatedAt: string;\n    }>\n  >`\n    select\n      rate_bps as \"rateBps\",\n      set_by as \"setBy\",\n      created_at::text as \"createdAt\",\n      updated_at::text as \"updatedAt\"\n    from referral_kol_rates\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n    limit 1\n  `;\n  return row ?? null;\n}\n\nasync function fetchReferralEarnings(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n): Promise<PeekReferralEarningsSummary> {\n  const [row] = await sql<\n    Array<{\n      earningsCount: number;\n      totalReferrerEarnedLamports: string;\n      totalRefereeRebateLamports: string;\n      lastEarnedAt: string | null;\n    }>\n  >`\n    select\n      count(*)::int as \"earningsCount\",\n      coalesce(sum(referrer_earned_lamports), 0)::text as \"totalReferrerEarnedLamports\",\n      coalesce(sum(referee_rebate_lamports), 0)::text as \"totalRefereeRebateLamports\",\n      max(created_at)::text as \"lastEarnedAt\"\n    from referral_earnings\n    where referrer_user_id = ${userId} or referee_user_id = ${userId}\n  `;\n  return (\n    row ?? {\n      earningsCount: 0,\n      totalReferrerEarnedLamports: \"0\",\n      totalRefereeRebateLamports: \"0\",\n      lastEarnedAt: null,\n    }\n  );\n}\n\nasync function fetchRecentReferralClaims(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n  limit: number,\n): Promise<ReadonlyArray<PeekReferralClaimRow>> {\n  return sql<Array<PeekReferralClaimRow>>`\n    select\n      id::text as \"id\",\n      amount_lamports::text as \"amountLamports\",\n      status,\n      retry_count as \"retryCount\",\n      tx_signature as \"txSignature\",\n      error,\n      requested_at::text as \"requestedAt\",\n      processed_at::text as \"processedAt\"\n    from referral_claims\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n    order by requested_at desc\n    limit ${limit}\n  `;\n}\n\nasync function fetchPlayerPoints(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n): Promise<PeekPlayerPoints> {\n  const [row] = await sql<\n    Array<{\n      balance: string;\n      lifetimeEarned: string;\n      updatedAt: string;\n    }>\n  >`\n    select\n      balance::text as \"balance\",\n      lifetime_earned::text as \"lifetimeEarned\",\n      updated_at::text as \"updatedAt\"\n    from player_points\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n    limit 1\n  `;\n  return (\n    row ?? {\n      balance: \"0\",\n      lifetimeEarned: \"0\",\n      updatedAt: null,\n    }\n  );\n}\n\nasync function fetchRecentPointGrants(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n  limit: number,\n): Promise<ReadonlyArray<PeekPointGrantRow>> {\n  return sql<Array<PeekPointGrantRow>>`\n    select\n      id::text as \"id\",\n      source_type as \"sourceType\",\n      source_id as \"sourceId\",\n      amount::text as \"amount\",\n      created_at::text as \"createdAt\"\n    from point_grants\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n    order by created_at desc\n    limit ${limit}\n  `;\n}\n\nasync function fetchRecentCrateDrops(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n  limit: number,\n): Promise<ReadonlyArray<PeekCrateDropRow>> {\n  return sql<Array<PeekCrateDropRow>>`\n    select\n      id::text as \"id\",\n      trigger_type as \"triggerType\",\n      trigger_id as \"triggerId\",\n      crate_type as \"crateType\",\n      contents_amount as \"contentsAmount\",\n      status,\n      created_at::text as \"createdAt\",\n      granted_at::text as \"grantedAt\"\n    from crate_drops\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n    order by created_at desc\n    limit ${limit}\n  `;\n}\n\nasync function fetchChallengeSummary(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n): Promise<PeekChallengeAssignmentSummary> {\n  const [row] = await sql<\n    Array<{\n      active: number;\n      completed: number;\n      expired: number;\n      total: number;\n    }>\n  >`\n    select\n      count(*) filter (where status = 'active')::int as \"active\",\n      count(*) filter (where status = 'completed')::int as \"completed\",\n      count(*) filter (where status = 'expired')::int as \"expired\",\n      count(*)::int as \"total\"\n    from challenge_assignments\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n  `;\n  return row ?? { active: 0, completed: 0, expired: 0, total: 0 };\n}\n\nasync function fetchRecentGameEntries(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n  limit: number,\n): Promise<ReadonlyArray<PeekGameEntryRow>> {\n  return sql<Array<PeekGameEntryRow>>`\n    select\n      id::text as \"id\",\n      game,\n      round_pda as \"roundPda\",\n      match_id as \"matchId\",\n      amount_lamports::text as \"amountLamports\",\n      side,\n      is_winner as \"isWinner\",\n      payout_lamports::text as \"payoutLamports\",\n      created_at::text as \"createdAt\",\n      settled_at::text as \"settledAt\"\n    from game_entries\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n    order by created_at desc\n    limit ${limit}\n  `;\n}\n\nasync function fetchRecentTransactions(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n  limit: number,\n): Promise<ReadonlyArray<PeekTransactionRow>> {\n  return sql<Array<PeekTransactionRow>>`\n    select\n      id::text as \"id\",\n      game,\n      match_id as \"matchId\",\n      tx_type as \"txType\",\n      amount_lamports::text as \"amountLamports\",\n      tx_sig as \"txSig\",\n      created_at::text as \"createdAt\"\n    from transactions\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n    order by created_at desc\n    limit ${limit}\n  `;\n}\n\nasync function fetchFraudFlags(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n  limit: number,\n): Promise<ReadonlyArray<PeekFraudFlagRow>> {\n  return sql<Array<PeekFraudFlagRow>>`\n    select\n      id::text as \"id\",\n      flag_type as \"flagType\",\n      status,\n      related_id as \"relatedId\",\n      created_at::text as \"createdAt\",\n      resolved_at::text as \"resolvedAt\"\n    from fraud_flags\n    where user_id = ${userId}\n    order by created_at desc\n    limit ${limit}\n  `;\n}\n\nasync function fetchRecentUserQueueEvents(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n  wallet: string,\n  limit: number,\n): Promise<ReadonlyArray<PeekUserQueueEventRow>> {\n  // event_queue has no user_id column; join via JSONB payload identifiers that\n  // every backend writer uses today (`userId`, `user_id`, `wallet`). Bounded by\n  // limit so the admin page never streams the full queue.\n  return sql<Array<PeekUserQueueEventRow>>`\n    select\n      id::text as \"id\",\n      event_type as \"eventType\",\n      status,\n      attempts,\n      max_attempts as \"maxAttempts\",\n      scheduled_at::text as \"scheduledAt\",\n      created_at::text as \"createdAt\",\n      error\n    from event_queue\n    where payload->>'userId' = ${userId}\n       or payload->>'user_id' = ${userId}\n       or payload->>'wallet' = ${wallet}\n    order by created_at desc\n    limit ${limit}\n  `;\n}\n\nasync function fetchSelfReferralIndicator(\n  sql: Sql,\n  userId: string,\n): Promise<{ selfReferral: boolean }> {\n  const [row] = await sql<Array<{ selfReferral: boolean }>>`\n    select exists (\n      select 1\n      from referral_links rl\n      where rl.referrer_user_id = ${userId}\n        and rl.referee_user_id = ${userId}\n    ) as \"selfReferral\"\n  `;\n  return row ?? { selfReferral: false };\n}\n\nfunction computeAttention(input: {\n  recentReferralClaims: ReadonlyArray<PeekReferralClaimRow>;\n  recentUserQueueEvents: ReadonlyArray<PeekUserQueueEventRow>;\n  fraudFlags: ReadonlyArray<PeekFraudFlagRow>;\n  recentCrateDrops: ReadonlyArray<PeekCrateDropRow>;\n  selfReferralRow: { selfReferral: boolean };\n}): PeekUserAttentionFlags {\n  return {\n    failedClaim: input.recentReferralClaims.some(\n      (claim) => claim.status === \"failed\" || claim.status === \"error\",\n    ),\n    deadQueueEvent: input.recentUserQueueEvents.some(\n      (event) => event.status === \"dead\",\n    ),\n    activeFraudFlag: input.fraudFlags.some((flag) => flag.status === \"open\"),\n    pendingSolCratePayout: input.recentCrateDrops.some(\n      (drop) => drop.crateType === \"sol\" && drop.status === \"pending\",\n    ),\n    suspiciousReferralLoop: input.selfReferralRow.selfReferral,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Component: `user-detail-view.tsx`\n\n```typescript\nimport type { CSSProperties, ReactNode } from \"react\";\nimport Link from \"next/link\";\nimport type {\n  PeekChallengeAssignmentSummary,\n  PeekCrateDropRow,\n  PeekFraudFlagRow,\n  PeekGameEntryRow,\n  PeekKolRate,\n  PeekLinkedAccountRow,\n  PeekPlayerPoints,\n  PeekPointGrantRow,\n  PeekReferralClaimRow,\n  PeekReferralEarningsSummary,\n  PeekStatusTone,\n  PeekTelegramLinkTokenRow,\n  PeekTransactionRow,\n  PeekUserAttentionFlags,\n  PeekUserDetail,\n  PeekUserQueueEventRow,\n} from \"../lib/types/peek\";\nimport { DetailPanel, type PeekDetailSection } from \"./detail-panel\";\nimport { EmptyState } from \"./empty-state\";\nimport { StatusChip } from \"./status-chip\";\n\nexport type UserDetailViewProps = {\n  detail: PeekUserDetail;\n  activeSectionId?: string | null;\n};\n\nexport const USER_DETAIL_SECTION_IDS = [\n  \"identity\",\n  \"linked-accounts\",\n  \"referrals\",\n  \"games\",\n  \"rewards\",\n  \"challenges\",\n  \"transactions\",\n  \"attention\",\n] as const;\n\nexport type UserDetailSectionId = (typeof USER_DETAIL_SECTION_IDS)[number];\n\nexport function UserDetailView({\n  detail,\n  activeSectionId = null,\n}: UserDetailViewProps) {\n  const sections: ReadonlyArray<PeekDetailSection> = [\n    {\n      id: \"identity\",\n      label: \"Identity\",\n      body: <IdentitySection detail={detail} />,\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"linked-accounts\",\n      label: \"Linked accounts\",\n      body: <LinkedAccountsSection detail={detail} />,\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"referrals\",\n      label: \"Referrals\",\n      body: <ReferralsSection detail={detail} />,\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"games\",\n      label: \"Games\",\n      body: <GamesSection detail={detail} />,\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"rewards\",\n      label: \"Rewards\",\n      body: <RewardsSection detail={detail} />,\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"challenges\",\n      label: \"Challenges\",\n      body: <ChallengesSection summary={detail.challengeSummary} />,\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"transactions\",\n      label: \"Transactions\",\n      body: <TransactionsSection detail={detail} />,\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"attention\",\n      label: \"Attention\",\n      body: <AttentionSection detail={detail} />,\n    },\n  ];\n\n  return (\n    <article style={pageStyle} aria-label=\"User detail\">\n      <UserHeader detail={detail} />\n      <AttentionStrip flags={detail.attention} />\n      <DetailPanel\n        sections={sections}\n        activeId={activeSectionId}\n        ariaLabel=\"User detail sections\"\n      />\n    </article>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction UserHeader({ detail }: { detail: PeekUserDetail }) {\n  const heading = detail.user.username ?? detail.user.userId;\n  return (\n    <header style={headerStyle}>\n      <div>\n        <h1 style={headingStyle}>{heading}</h1>\n        <p style={walletStyle}>{detail.user.wallet}</p>\n      </div>\n      <dl style={metaStyle}>\n        <MetaPair label=\"user_id\" value={detail.user.userId} />\n        <MetaPair label=\"joined\" value={detail.user.joinedAt} />\n      </dl>\n    </header>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction MetaPair({ label, value }: { label: string; value: string }) {\n  return (\n    <div style={metaPairStyle}>\n      <dt style={metaLabelStyle}>{label}</dt>\n      <dd style={metaValueStyle}>{value}</dd>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction AttentionStrip({ flags }: { flags: PeekUserAttentionFlags }) {\n  const items = buildAttentionItems(flags);\n  if (items.length === 0) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return (\n    <aside aria-label=\"Attention\" style={attentionStripStyle}>\n      <span style={attentionLabelStyle}>Attention:</span>\n      {items.map((item) => (\n        <StatusChip\n          key={item.id}\n          label={item.label}\n          tone={item.tone}\n          title={item.description}\n        />\n      ))}\n    </aside>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction IdentitySection({ detail }: { detail: PeekUserDetail }) {\n  const rows: Array<[string, string | null]> = [\n    [\"user_id\", detail.user.userId],\n    [\"username\", detail.user.username],\n    [\"wallet\", detail.user.wallet],\n    [\"joined\", detail.user.joinedAt],\n    [\"avatar_url\", detail.user.avatarUrl],\n    [\"heat_multiplier\", detail.user.heatMultiplier],\n    [\"profile_points_balance\", detail.user.profilePointsBalance],\n  ];\n  return (\n    <DefinitionList\n      rows={rows}\n      empty=\"No identity recorded for this user.\"\n    />\n  );\n}\n\nfunction LinkedAccountsSection({ detail }: { detail: PeekUserDetail }) {\n  return (\n    <div style={stackStyle}>\n      <SubSection title=\"Telegram link state\">\n        <DefinitionList\n          rows={[\n            [\"state\", detail.telegram.state],\n            [\"telegram_user_id\", detail.telegram.telegramUserId],\n            [\"telegram_username\", detail.telegram.telegramUsername],\n          ]}\n        />\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"Linked accounts\">\n        {detail.linkedAccounts.length === 0 ? (\n          <EmptyState\n            state={{\n              title: \"No linked accounts.\",\n              body: \"This user has not linked any external provider accounts.\",\n            }}\n          />\n        ) : (\n          <SimpleTable\n            head={[\n              \"provider\",\n              \"provider_account_id\",\n              \"status\",\n              \"telegram_username\",\n              \"linked_at\",\n            ]}\n            rows={detail.linkedAccounts.map((row: PeekLinkedAccountRow) => [\n              row.provider,\n              row.providerAccountId,\n              <StatusChip\n                key=\"status\"\n                label={row.status}\n                tone={\n                  row.status === \"active\"\n                    ? \"positive\"\n                    : row.status === \"revoked\"\n                    ? \"negative\"\n                    : \"neutral\"\n                }\n              />,\n              row.telegramUsername ?? \"—\",\n              row.linkedAt,\n            ])}\n          />\n        )}\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"Recent Telegram link tokens\">\n        {detail.recentTelegramLinkTokens.length === 0 ? (\n          <EmptyState\n            state={{\n              title: \"No Telegram link tokens issued.\",\n              body: null,\n            }}\n          />\n        ) : (\n          <SimpleTable\n            head={[\n              \"status\",\n              \"telegram_user_id\",\n              \"telegram_username\",\n              \"expires_at\",\n              \"redeemed_at\",\n              \"created_at\",\n            ]}\n            rows={detail.recentTelegramLinkTokens.map(\n              (row: PeekTelegramLinkTokenRow) => [\n                <StatusChip\n                  key=\"status\"\n                  label={row.status}\n                  tone={\n                    row.status === \"redeemed\"\n                      ? \"positive\"\n                      : row.status === \"expired\"\n                      ? \"warning\"\n                      : \"neutral\"\n                  }\n                />,\n                row.telegramUserId ?? \"—\",\n                row.telegramUsername ?? \"—\",\n                row.expiresAt,\n                row.redeemedAt ?? \"—\",\n                row.createdAt,\n              ],\n            )}\n          />\n        )}\n      </SubSection>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction ReferralsSection({ detail }: { detail: PeekUserDetail }) {\n  const inboundLabel =\n    detail.inboundReferral.referrerCode ??\n    detail.inboundReferral.referrerUserId ??\n    \"No referrer\";\n  return (\n    <div style={stackStyle}>\n      <SubSection title=\"Inbound referral\">\n        <DefinitionList\n          rows={[\n            [\"referrer\", inboundLabel],\n            [\"referrer_user_id\", detail.inboundReferral.referrerUserId],\n            [\"linked_at\", detail.inboundReferral.linkedAt],\n          ]}\n        />\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"Referral code\">\n        <DefinitionList\n          rows={[\n            [\"referral_code\", detail.user.referralCode],\n            [\"referee_count\", String(detail.user.refereeCount)],\n          ]}\n        />\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"KOL rate\">\n        <KolRateBlock rate={detail.kolRate} />\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"Earnings & rebates\">\n        <EarningsBlock summary={detail.referralEarnings} />\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"Recent referral claims\">\n        {detail.recentReferralClaims.length === 0 ? (\n          <EmptyState state={{ title: \"No referral claims yet.\", body: null }} />\n        ) : (\n          <SimpleTable\n            head={[\n              \"amount_lamports\",\n              \"status\",\n              \"retry_count\",\n              \"tx_signature\",\n              \"requested_at\",\n              \"processed_at\",\n              \"error\",\n            ]}\n            rows={detail.recentReferralClaims.map(\n              (row: PeekReferralClaimRow) => [\n                row.amountLamports,\n                <StatusChip\n                  key=\"status\"\n                  label={row.status}\n                  tone={\n                    row.status === \"paid\"\n                      ? \"positive\"\n                      : row.status === \"failed\" || row.status === \"error\"\n                      ? \"negative\"\n                      : row.status === \"processing\"\n                      ? \"info\"\n                      : \"neutral\"\n                  }\n                />,\n                String(row.retryCount),\n                row.txSignature ?? \"—\",\n                row.requestedAt,\n                row.processedAt ?? \"—\",\n                row.error ?? \"—\",\n              ],\n            )}\n          />\n        )}\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"Outbound referees\">\n        {detail.outboundReferees.length === 0 ? (\n          <EmptyState state={{ title: \"No referees yet.\", body: null }} />\n        ) : (\n          <SimpleTable\n            head={[\"referee_user_id\", \"username\", \"linked_at\"]}\n            rows={detail.outboundReferees.map((row) => [\n              <Link key=\"link\" href={`/users/${row.refereeUserId}`} style={linkStyle}>\n                {row.refereeUserId}\n              </Link>,\n              row.refereeUsername ?? \"—\",\n              row.createdAt,\n            ])}\n          />\n        )}\n      </SubSection>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction GamesSection({ detail }: { detail: PeekUserDetail }) {\n  if (detail.recentGameEntries.length === 0) {\n    return (\n      <EmptyState\n        state={{\n          title: \"No game entries yet.\",\n          body: \"This user has not entered any FlipYou, Pot Shot, or Close Call rounds.\",\n        }}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n  return (\n    <SimpleTable\n      head={[\n        \"game\",\n        \"match_id\",\n        \"amount_lamports\",\n        \"side\",\n        \"is_winner\",\n        \"payout_lamports\",\n        \"created_at\",\n        \"settled_at\",\n      ]}\n      rows={detail.recentGameEntries.map((row: PeekGameEntryRow) => [\n        <StatusChip key=\"game\" label={row.game} tone=\"info\" />,\n        <Link\n          key=\"match\"\n          href={`/games/${row.game}/rounds/${row.roundPda}`}\n          style={linkStyle}\n        >\n          {row.matchId}\n        </Link>,\n        row.amountLamports,\n        row.side ?? \"—\",\n        renderWinner(row.isWinner),\n        row.payoutLamports,\n        row.createdAt,\n        row.settledAt ?? \"—\",\n      ])}\n    />\n  );\n}\n\nfunction RewardsSection({ detail }: { detail: PeekUserDetail }) {\n  return (\n    <div style={stackStyle}>\n      <SubSection title=\"Points balance\">\n        <PointsBlock points={detail.points} />\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"Recent point grants\">\n        {detail.recentPointGrants.length === 0 ? (\n          <EmptyState state={{ title: \"No point grants recorded.\", body: null }} />\n        ) : (\n          <SimpleTable\n            head={[\"source_type\", \"source_id\", \"amount\", \"created_at\"]}\n            rows={detail.recentPointGrants.map((row: PeekPointGrantRow) => [\n              row.sourceType,\n              row.sourceId,\n              row.amount,\n              row.createdAt,\n            ])}\n          />\n        )}\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"Recent crate drops\">\n        {detail.recentCrateDrops.length === 0 ? (\n          <EmptyState state={{ title: \"No crate drops recorded.\", body: null }} />\n        ) : (\n          <SimpleTable\n            head={[\n              \"trigger_type\",\n              \"trigger_id\",\n              \"crate_type\",\n              \"contents_amount\",\n              \"status\",\n              \"created_at\",\n              \"granted_at\",\n            ]}\n            rows={detail.recentCrateDrops.map((row: PeekCrateDropRow) => [\n              row.triggerType,\n              row.triggerId,\n              row.crateType,\n              row.contentsAmount,\n              <StatusChip\n                key=\"status\"\n                label={row.status}\n                tone={\n                  row.status === \"granted\"\n                    ? \"positive\"\n                    : row.status === \"pending\"\n                    ? \"warning\"\n                    : row.status === \"failed\"\n                    ? \"negative\"\n                    : \"neutral\"\n                }\n              />,\n              row.createdAt,\n              row.grantedAt ?? \"—\",\n            ])}\n          />\n        )}\n      </SubSection>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction ChallengesSection({\n  summary,\n}: {\n  summary: PeekChallengeAssignmentSummary;\n}) {\n  if (summary.total === 0) {\n    return (\n      <EmptyState\n        state={{\n          title: \"No challenge assignments.\",\n          body: \"This user has not been assigned any challenges yet.\",\n        }}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n  return (\n    <DefinitionList\n      rows={[\n        [\"active\", String(summary.active)],\n        [\"completed\", String(summary.completed)],\n        [\"expired\", String(summary.expired)],\n        [\"total\", String(summary.total)],\n      ]}\n    />\n  );\n}\n\nfunction TransactionsSection({ detail }: { detail: PeekUserDetail }) {\n  if (detail.recentTransactions.length === 0) {\n    return (\n      <EmptyState\n        state={{\n          title: \"No transactions recorded.\",\n          body: \"This user has no on-chain transaction records yet.\",\n        }}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n  return (\n    <SimpleTable\n      head={[\n        \"game\",\n        \"match_id\",\n        \"tx_type\",\n        \"amount_lamports\",\n        \"tx_sig\",\n        \"created_at\",\n      ]}\n      rows={detail.recentTransactions.map((row: PeekTransactionRow) => [\n        <StatusChip key=\"game\" label={row.game} tone=\"info\" />,\n        row.matchId,\n        <StatusChip\n          key=\"type\"\n          label={row.txType}\n          tone={\n            row.txType === \"payout\"\n              ? \"positive\"\n              : row.txType === \"refund\"\n              ? \"warning\"\n              : \"neutral\"\n          }\n        />,\n        row.amountLamports,\n        row.txSig,\n        row.createdAt,\n      ])}\n    />\n  );\n}\n\nfunction AttentionSection({ detail }: { detail: PeekUserDetail }) {\n  const items = buildAttentionItems(detail.attention);\n  return (\n    <div style={stackStyle}>\n      <SubSection title=\"Attention flags\">\n        {items.length === 0 ? (\n          <EmptyState\n            state={{\n              title: \"No attention flags.\",\n              body: \"Nothing currently flagged for review on this user.\",\n            }}\n          />\n        ) : (\n          <ul style={attentionListStyle}>\n            {items.map((item) => (\n              <li key={item.id} style={attentionItemStyle}>\n                <StatusChip label={item.label} tone={item.tone} />\n                <span style={attentionDescStyle}>{item.description}</span>\n              </li>\n            ))}\n          </ul>\n        )}\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"Open fraud flags\">\n        {detail.fraudFlags.length === 0 ? (\n          <EmptyState state={{ title: \"No fraud flags.\", body: null }} />\n        ) : (\n          <SimpleTable\n            head={[\"flag_type\", \"status\", \"related_id\", \"created_at\", \"resolved_at\"]}\n            rows={detail.fraudFlags.map((row: PeekFraudFlagRow) => [\n              row.flagType,\n              <StatusChip\n                key=\"status\"\n                label={row.status}\n                tone={\n                  row.status === \"open\"\n                    ? \"negative\"\n                    : row.status === \"reviewed\"\n                    ? \"info\"\n                    : \"neutral\"\n                }\n              />,\n              row.relatedId ?? \"—\",\n              row.createdAt,\n              row.resolvedAt ?? \"—\",\n            ])}\n          />\n        )}\n      </SubSection>\n\n      <SubSection title=\"Recent queue events\">\n        {detail.recentUserQueueEvents.length === 0 ? (\n          <EmptyState state={{ title: \"No queue events for this user.\", body: null }} />\n        ) : (\n          <SimpleTable\n            head={[\n              \"event_type\",\n              \"status\",\n              \"attempts\",\n              \"scheduled_at\",\n              \"created_at\",\n              \"error\",\n            ]}\n            rows={detail.recentUserQueueEvents.map(\n              (row: PeekUserQueueEventRow) => [\n                row.eventType,\n                <StatusChip\n                  key=\"status\"\n                  label={row.status}\n                  tone={\n                    row.status === \"dead\"\n                      ? \"negative\"\n                      : row.status === \"failed\"\n                      ? \"warning\"\n                      : row.status === \"processed\"\n                      ? \"positive\"\n                      : \"neutral\"\n                  }\n                />,\n                `${row.attempts} / ${row.maxAttempts}`,\n                row.scheduledAt,\n                row.createdAt,\n                row.error ?? \"—\",\n              ],\n            )}\n          />\n        )}\n      </SubSection>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n// --- Reusable building blocks ------------------------------------------------\n\nfunction SubSection({\n  title,\n  children,\n}: {\n  title: string;\n  children: ReactNode;\n}) {\n  return (\n    <section style={subSectionStyle}>\n      <h3 style={subHeadingStyle}>{title}</h3>\n      {children}\n    </section>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction DefinitionList({\n  rows,\n  empty,\n}: {\n  rows: ReadonlyArray<readonly [string, string | null]>;\n  empty?: string;\n}) {\n  const usable = rows.filter(([, value]) => value !== null && value !== \"\");\n  if (usable.length === 0) {\n    return (\n      <EmptyState\n        state={{\n          title: empty ?? \"No data recorded for this section.\",\n          body: null,\n        }}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n  return (\n    <dl style={dlStyle}>\n      {rows.map(([label, value]) => (\n        <div key={label} style={dlRowStyle}>\n          <dt style={dlLabelStyle}>{label}</dt>\n          <dd style={dlValueStyle}>{value ?? \"—\"}</dd>\n        </div>\n      ))}\n    </dl>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction SimpleTable({\n  head,\n  rows,\n}: {\n  head: ReadonlyArray<string>;\n  rows: ReadonlyArray<ReadonlyArray<ReactNode>>;\n}) {\n  return (\n    <div style={tableWrapperStyle}>\n      <table style={tableStyle}>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            {head.map((label) => (\n              <th key={label} style={thStyle}>\n                {label}\n              </th>\n            ))}\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          {rows.map((row, rowIndex) => (\n            <tr key={rowIndex}>\n              {row.map((cell, cellIndex) => (\n                <td key={cellIndex} style={tdStyle}>\n                  {cell}\n                </td>\n              ))}\n            </tr>\n          ))}\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\nfunction KolRateBlock({ rate }: { rate: PeekKolRate | null }) {\n  if (!rate) {\n    return (\n      <EmptyState\n        state={{ title: \"Not a KOL.\", body: \"No KOL rate configured for this user.\" }}\n      />\n    );\n  }\n  return (\n    <DefinitionList\n      rows={[\n        [\"rate_bps\", String(rate.rateBps)],\n        [\"set_by\", rate.setBy],\n        [\"created_at\", rate.createdAt],\n        [\"updated_at\", rate.updatedAt],\n      ]}\n    />\n  );\n}\n\nfunction EarningsBlock({\n  summary,\n}: {\n  summary: PeekReferralEarningsSummary;\n}) {\n  if (summary.earningsCount === 0) {\n    return (\n      <EmptyState state={{ title: \"No referral earnings yet.\", body: null }} />\n    );\n  }\n  return (\n    <DefinitionList\n      rows={[\n        [\"earnings_count\", String(summary.earningsCount)],\n        [\"total_referrer_earned_lamports\", summary.totalReferrerEarnedLamports],\n        [\"total_referee_rebate_lamports\", summary.totalRefereeRebateLamports],\n        [\"last_earned_at\", summary.lastEarnedAt],\n      ]}\n    />\n  );\n}\n\nfunction PointsBlock({ points }: { points: PeekPlayerPoints }) {\n  return (\n    <DefinitionList\n      rows={[\n        [\"balance\", points.balance],\n        [\"lifetime_earned\", points.lifetimeEarned],\n        [\"updated_at\", points.updatedAt],\n      ]}\n    />\n  );\n}\n\nfunction renderWinner(value: boolean | null): string {\n  if (value === null) return \"—\";\n  return value ? \"win\" : \"loss\";\n}\n\ntype AttentionItem = {\n  id: string;\n  label: string;\n  tone: PeekStatusTone;\n  description: string;\n};\n\nfunction buildAttentionItems(\n  flags: PeekUserAttentionFlags,\n): ReadonlyArray<AttentionItem> {\n  const items: AttentionItem[] = [];\n  if (flags.failedClaim) {\n    items.push({\n      id: \"failed_claim\",\n      label: \"Failed claim\",\n      tone: \"negative\",\n      description: \"At least one recent referral claim is in failed/error status.\",\n    });\n  }\n  if (flags.deadQueueEvent) {\n    items.push({\n      id: \"dead_queue_event\",\n      label: \"Dead queue event\",\n      tone: \"negative\",\n      description: \"An async queue event for this user has hit max attempts.\",\n    });\n  }\n  if (flags.activeFraudFlag) {\n    items.push({\n      id: \"active_fraud_flag\",\n      label: \"Active fraud flag\",\n      tone: \"warning\",\n      description: \"An open fraud flag exists on this user and needs review.\",\n    });\n  }\n  if (flags.pendingSolCratePayout) {\n    items.push({\n      id: \"pending_sol_crate_payout\",\n      label: \"Pending SOL crate payout\",\n      tone: \"warning\",\n      description: \"A SOL crate drop is pending payout for this user.\",\n    });\n  }\n  if (flags.suspiciousReferralLoop) {\n    items.push({\n      id: \"suspicious_referral_loop\",\n      label: \"Suspicious referral self/loop\",\n      tone: \"negative\",\n      description:\n        \"This user appears as both referrer and referee on a referral_links row.\",\n    });\n  }\n  return items;\n}\n\n// --- Styles ------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nconst pageStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  display: \"grid\",\n  gap: \"1.25rem\",\n};\n\nconst headerStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  display: \"flex\",\n  flexWrap: \"wrap\",\n  gap: \"1rem\",\n  alignItems: \"flex-end\",\n  justifyContent: \"space-between\",\n  borderBottom: \"1px solid #1e293b\",\n  paddingBottom: \"1rem\",\n};\n\nconst headingStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  margin: 0,\n  fontSize: \"1.5rem\",\n  color: \"#e2e8f0\",\n};\n\nconst walletStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  margin: \"0.25rem 0 0\",\n  fontFamily: \"monospace\",\n  color: \"#94a3b8\",\n  fontSize: \"0.875rem\",\n};\n\nconst metaStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  margin: 0,\n  display: \"flex\",\n  flexWrap: \"wrap\",\n  gap: \"1rem\",\n};\n\nconst metaPairStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  display: \"grid\",\n  gap: \"0.125rem\",\n};\n\nconst metaLabelStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  margin: 0,\n  fontSize: \"0.6875rem\",\n  textTransform: \"uppercase\",\n  letterSpacing: \"0.05em\",\n  color: \"#94a3b8\",\n};\n\nconst metaValueStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  margin: 0,\n  fontSize: \"0.8125rem\",\n  fontFamily: \"monospace\",\n  color: \"#e2e8f0\",\n};\n\nconst attentionStripStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  display: \"flex\",\n  flexWrap: \"wrap\",\n  alignItems: \"center\",\n  gap: \"0.5rem\",\n  padding: \"0.5rem 0.75rem\",\n  borderRadius: \"0.5rem\",\n  background: \"#1f1305\",\n  border: \"1px solid #b45309\",\n};\n\nconst attentionLabelStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  fontSize: \"0.75rem\",\n  fontWeight: 600,\n  textTransform: \"uppercase\",\n  letterSpacing: \"0.05em\",\n  color: \"#fde68a\",\n};\n\nconst attentionListStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  listStyle: \"none\",\n  margin: 0,\n  padding: 0,\n  display: \"grid\",\n  gap: \"0.5rem\",\n};\n\nconst attentionItemStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  display: \"flex\",\n  alignItems: \"center\",\n  gap: \"0.5rem\",\n};\n\nconst attentionDescStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  fontSize: \"0.8125rem\",\n  color: \"#cbd5f5\",\n};\n\nconst stackStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  display: \"grid\",\n  gap: \"1rem\",\n};\n\nconst subSectionStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  display: \"grid\",\n  gap: \"0.5rem\",\n};\n\nconst subHeadingStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  margin: 0,\n  fontSize: \"0.875rem\",\n  fontWeight: 600,\n  color: \"#cbd5f5\",\n  textTransform: \"uppercase\",\n  letterSpacing: \"0.05em\",\n};\n\nconst dlStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  margin: 0,\n  display: \"grid\",\n  gridTemplateColumns: \"max-content 1fr\",\n  gap: \"0.25rem 1rem\",\n};\n\nconst dlRowStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  display: \"contents\",\n};\n\nconst dlLabelStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  margin: 0,\n  fontSize: \"0.6875rem\",\n  textTransform: \"uppercase\",\n  letterSpacing: \"0.05em\",\n  color: \"#94a3b8\",\n};\n\nconst dlValueStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  margin: 0,\n  fontSize: \"0.8125rem\",\n  fontFamily: \"monospace\",\n  color: \"#e2e8f0\",\n  overflowWrap: \"anywhere\",\n};\n\nconst tableWrapperStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  overflowX: \"auto\",\n  border: \"1px solid #1e293b\",\n  borderRadius: \"0.5rem\",\n};\n\nconst tableStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  width: \"100%\",\n  borderCollapse: \"collapse\",\n  fontSize: \"0.8125rem\",\n};\n\nconst thStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  textAlign: \"left\",\n  padding: \"0.5rem 0.75rem\",\n  background: \"#0b1220\",\n  color: \"#94a3b8\",\n  fontWeight: 600,\n  borderBottom: \"1px solid #1e293b\",\n  whiteSpace: \"nowrap\",\n};\n\nconst tdStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  padding: \"0.5rem 0.75rem\",\n  borderBottom: \"1px solid #1e293b\",\n  color: \"#e2e8f0\",\n  fontFamily: \"monospace\",\n  whiteSpace: \"nowrap\",\n};\n\nconst linkStyle: CSSProperties = {\n  color: \"#bfdbfe\",\n  textDecoration: \"underline\",\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Audit Writer: `writer.ts`\n\n```typescript\n// Server-only audit writer for peek (FR-11).\n//\n// Writes `peek.*` events into the existing `operator_events` table so internal\n// access (`peek.search`, `peek.user.view_sensitive`, `peek.export`,\n// `peek.access.denied`) and admin changes (`peek.change.applied`,\n// `peek.change.rejected`) leave a reviewable trail without a new migration.\n//\n// Behavior contract:\n// - Every payload runs through `redactPayload` before persistence; secrets\n//   never reach the DB.\n// - Inserts go to a single `operator_events` row keyed by `event_type`. The\n//   `pda` column is left null because peek audit records are not round-keyed.\n// - Insert failures are logged server-side and returned as a structured\n//   `{ ok: false, reason }`. The caller MUST NOT propagate the failure detail\n//   to the browser; sensitive data must not leak through error rendering.\n\nimport type { Sql } from \"postgres\";\nimport {\n  type PeekAuditEventType,\n  type PeekAuditPayload,\n} from \"../../lib/types/peek\";\nimport { getSqlClient } from \"../db/client\";\nimport { redactPayload } from \"./redact\";\n\nexport type PeekAuditInput = {\n  eventType: PeekAuditEventType;\n  payload: PeekAuditPayload;\n};\n\nexport type PeekAuditWriteResult =\n  | { ok: true }\n  | { ok: false; reason: \"invalid_payload\" | \"insert_failed\" };\n\nexport type PeekAuditWriterOptions = {\n  sql?: Sql;\n  logger?: (message: string, context: Record<string, unknown>) => void;\n};\n\nfunction defaultLogger(\n  message: string,\n  context: Record<string, unknown>,\n): void {\n  // Server-only console logging; never returned to the browser.\n  console.error(message, context);\n}\n\nexport async function writePeekAuditEvent(\n  input: PeekAuditInput,\n  options: PeekAuditWriterOptions = {},\n): Promise<PeekAuditWriteResult> {\n  if (!input.payload.actorEmail) {\n    return { ok: false, reason: \"invalid_payload\" };\n  }\n\n  const safePayload = redactPayload(input.payload);\n  const sql = options.sql ?? getSqlClient();\n  const logger = options.logger ?? defaultLogger;\n\n  try {\n    await sql`\n      insert into operator_events (event_type, payload)\n      values (${input.eventType}, ${sql.json(\n        safePayload as unknown as Parameters<typeof sql.json>[0],\n      )})\n    `;\n    return { ok: true };\n  } catch (error) {\n    logger(\"[peek-audit] insert failed\", {\n      eventType: input.eventType,\n      message: error instanceof Error ? error.message : \"unknown\",\n    });\n    return { ok: false, reason: \"insert_failed\" };\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Audit Writer Test Pattern: `writer.test.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, expect, it, vi } from \"vitest\";\nimport type { Sql } from \"postgres\";\nimport {\n  PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED,\n  type PeekAuditPayload,\n} from \"../../../lib/types/peek\";\nimport { writePeekAuditEvent } from \"../writer\";\n\ntype SqlCall = { strings: ReadonlyArray<string>; values: ReadonlyArray<unknown> };\n\ntype SqlMock = {\n  sql: Sql;\n  calls: ReadonlyArray<SqlCall>;\n  jsonArgs: ReadonlyArray<unknown>;\n};\n\nconst JSON_SENTINEL = Symbol(\"peek-audit-json\");\n\nfunction createSqlMock(options: { error?: Error } = {}): SqlMock {\n  const calls: SqlCall[] = [];\n  const jsonArgs: unknown[] = [];\n\n  const fn = (strings: TemplateStringsArray, ...values: unknown[]) => {\n    calls.push({ strings: [...strings], values: [...values] });\n    if (options.error) return Promise.reject(options.error);\n    return Promise.resolve([]);\n  };\n\n  const sql = Object.assign(fn, {\n    json(value: unknown) {\n      jsonArgs.push(value);\n      return { [JSON_SENTINEL]: value };\n    },\n  }) as unknown as Sql;\n\n  return { sql, calls, jsonArgs };\n}\n\nfunction basePayload(\n  overrides: Partial<PeekAuditPayload> = {},\n): PeekAuditPayload {\n  return {\n    actorEmail: \"alice@example.com\",\n    route: null,\n    actionId: null,\n    resourceType: null,\n    resourceId: null,\n    filterSummary: null,\n    resultCount: null,\n    requestId: null,\n    rejectionReason: null,\n    changes: null,\n    ...overrides,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction persistedPayload(mock: SqlMock): PeekAuditPayload {\n  expect(mock.jsonArgs).toHaveLength(1);\n  return mock.jsonArgs[0] as PeekAuditPayload;\n}\n\ndescribe(\"writePeekAuditEvent\", () => {\n  it(\"persists a sensitive read with the full FR-11 payload\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock();\n\n    const result = await writePeekAuditEvent(\n      {\n        eventType: \"peek.user.view_sensitive\",\n        payload: basePayload({\n          route: \"/users/u-1\",\n          actionId: \"user.view_sensitive\",\n          resourceType: \"user\",\n          resourceId: \"u-1\",\n          filterSummary: \"tab=identity\",\n          resultCount: 1,\n          requestId: \"req-123\",\n        }),\n      },\n      { sql: mock.sql },\n    );\n\n    expect(result).toEqual({ ok: true });\n    expect(mock.calls).toHaveLength(1);\n    const insert = mock.calls[0];\n    expect(insert.strings.join(\" \")).toMatch(/insert into operator_events/i);\n    expect(insert.values[0]).toBe(\"peek.user.view_sensitive\");\n\n    const stored = persistedPayload(mock);\n    expect(stored).toEqual({\n      actorEmail: \"alice@example.com\",\n      route: \"/users/u-1\",\n      actionId: \"user.view_sensitive\",\n      resourceType: \"user\",\n      resourceId: \"u-1\",\n      filterSummary: \"tab=identity\",\n      resultCount: 1,\n      requestId: \"req-123\",\n      rejectionReason: null,\n      changes: null,\n    });\n  });\n\n  it(\"persists an export event with result-count and filter summary\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock();\n\n    const result = await writePeekAuditEvent(\n      {\n        eventType: \"peek.export\",\n        payload: basePayload({\n          route: \"/growth/referrals/export\",\n          actionId: \"referrers.export\",\n          resourceType: \"export\",\n          resourceId: null,\n          filterSummary: \"status=pending&from=2026-04-01\",\n          resultCount: 142,\n          requestId: \"req-export-7\",\n        }),\n      },\n      { sql: mock.sql },\n    );\n\n    expect(result).toEqual({ ok: true });\n    expect(mock.calls[0]?.values[0]).toBe(\"peek.export\");\n\n    const stored = persistedPayload(mock);\n    expect(stored.actorEmail).toBe(\"alice@example.com\");\n    expect(stored.actionId).toBe(\"referrers.export\");\n    expect(stored.resultCount).toBe(142);\n    expect(stored.filterSummary).toBe(\"status=pending&from=2026-04-01\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"persists an access-denied event with the route and rejection reason\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock();\n\n    const result = await writePeekAuditEvent(\n      {\n        eventType: \"peek.access.denied\",\n        payload: basePayload({\n          route: \"/audit\",\n          actionId: null,\n          rejectionReason: \"role_required:admin\",\n          resourceType: \"route\",\n          resourceId: \"/audit\",\n        }),\n      },\n      { sql: mock.sql },\n    );\n\n    expect(result).toEqual({ ok: true });\n    expect(mock.calls[0]?.values[0]).toBe(\"peek.access.denied\");\n\n    const stored = persistedPayload(mock);\n    expect(stored.rejectionReason).toBe(\"role_required:admin\");\n    expect(stored.route).toBe(\"/audit\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"persists a mutation-applied event with before/after changes\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock();\n\n    const result = await writePeekAuditEvent(\n      {\n        eventType: \"peek.change.applied\",\n        payload: basePayload({\n          route: \"/growth/kol\",\n          actionId: \"kol_rate.update\",\n          resourceType: \"referral_kol_rates\",\n          resourceId: \"kol-7\",\n          changes: [\n            { field: \"rate_bps\", before: 1000, after: 1500 },\n            { field: \"set_by\", before: \"alice@example.com\", after: \"alice@example.com\" },\n          ],\n        }),\n      },\n      { sql: mock.sql },\n    );\n\n    expect(result).toEqual({ ok: true });\n    expect(mock.calls[0]?.values[0]).toBe(\"peek.change.applied\");\n\n    const stored = persistedPayload(mock);\n    expect(stored.changes).toEqual([\n      { field: \"rate_bps\", before: 1000, after: 1500 },\n      { field: \"set_by\", before: \"alice@example.com\", after: \"alice@example.com\" },\n    ]);\n  });\n\n  it(\"persists a mutation-rejected event with the rejection reason and no submitted secrets\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock();\n\n    const result = await writePeekAuditEvent(\n      {\n        eventType: \"peek.change.rejected\",\n        payload: basePayload({\n          route: \"/economy/rewards\",\n          actionId: \"reward_config.update\",\n          resourceType: \"reward_config\",\n          resourceId: \"max_daily_payout_lamports\",\n          rejectionReason: \"value_out_of_range\",\n          changes: [\n            { field: \"value\", before: \"100000\", after: \"999999999999\" },\n          ],\n        }),\n      },\n      { sql: mock.sql },\n    );\n\n    expect(result).toEqual({ ok: true });\n    expect(mock.calls[0]?.values[0]).toBe(\"peek.change.rejected\");\n\n    const stored = persistedPayload(mock);\n    expect(stored.rejectionReason).toBe(\"value_out_of_range\");\n    expect(stored.changes?.[0]?.after).toBe(\"999999999999\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"redacts JWT tokens, DB URLs, private keys, Bearer headers, and CF access headers before persisting\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock();\n\n    const jwt =\n      \"eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJhbGljZSJ9.signaturesignaturesignature\";\n    const dbUrl = \"postgresql://user:pw@db.internal:5432/peek?sslmode=require\";\n    const privateKey = \"-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\\nABCDEF\\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\";\n    const bearer = \"Bearer abc123def456ghi789\";\n    const cfHeader = \"cf-access-jwt-assertion: somevalue\";\n\n    const result = await writePeekAuditEvent(\n      {\n        eventType: \"peek.search\",\n        payload: basePayload({\n          route: dbUrl,\n          actionId: bearer,\n          resourceType: \"search\",\n          resourceId: jwt,\n          filterSummary: cfHeader,\n          requestId: privateKey,\n          changes: [\n            { field: \"token\", before: jwt, after: \"harmless\" },\n            { field: \"conn\", before: \"harmless\", after: dbUrl },\n          ],\n        }),\n      },\n      { sql: mock.sql },\n    );\n\n    expect(result).toEqual({ ok: true });\n    const stored = persistedPayload(mock);\n\n    expect(stored.route).toBe(PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED);\n    expect(stored.actionId).toBe(PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED);\n    expect(stored.resourceId).toBe(PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED);\n    expect(stored.filterSummary).toBe(PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED);\n    expect(stored.requestId).toBe(PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED);\n    expect(stored.changes).toEqual([\n      { field: \"token\", before: PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED, after: \"harmless\" },\n      { field: \"conn\", before: \"harmless\", after: PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED },\n    ]);\n\n    const serialized = JSON.stringify(stored);\n    expect(serialized).not.toContain(jwt);\n    expect(serialized).not.toContain(dbUrl);\n    expect(serialized).not.toContain(\"PRIVATE KEY\");\n    expect(serialized).not.toContain(\"Bearer \");\n    expect(serialized).not.toContain(\"cf-access-jwt-assertion\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"rejects payloads with an empty actor email without inserting a row\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock();\n\n    const result = await writePeekAuditEvent(\n      {\n        eventType: \"peek.search\",\n        payload: basePayload({ actorEmail: \"\" }),\n      },\n      { sql: mock.sql },\n    );\n\n    expect(result).toEqual({ ok: false, reason: \"invalid_payload\" });\n    expect(mock.calls).toHaveLength(0);\n    expect(mock.jsonArgs).toHaveLength(0);\n  });\n\n  it(\"returns insert_failed and logs the error when the DB rejects the insert\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock({\n      error: new Error(\"connection refused: postgres://hidden:secret@host\"),\n    });\n    const logger = vi.fn();\n\n    const result = await writePeekAuditEvent(\n      {\n        eventType: \"peek.export\",\n        payload: basePayload({ actionId: \"users.export\" }),\n      },\n      { sql: mock.sql, logger },\n    );\n\n    expect(result).toEqual({ ok: false, reason: \"insert_failed\" });\n    expect(logger).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);\n    const [message, context] = logger.mock.calls[0] ?? [];\n    expect(message).toBe(\"[peek-audit] insert failed\");\n    expect(context).toMatchObject({ eventType: \"peek.export\" });\n  });\n\n  it(\"does not propagate the underlying DB error to the caller\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock({\n      error: new Error(\"internal: schema=peek password=hunter2\"),\n    });\n    // Suppress the default console.error so the failure path stays quiet during the test.\n    const logger = vi.fn();\n\n    const result = await writePeekAuditEvent(\n      {\n        eventType: \"peek.access.denied\",\n        payload: basePayload(),\n      },\n      { sql: mock.sql, logger },\n    );\n\n    expect(result).toEqual({ ok: false, reason: \"insert_failed\" });\n    // The result is a closed union; \"insert_failed\" carries no error detail.\n    expect(JSON.stringify(result)).not.toContain(\"hunter2\");\n    expect(JSON.stringify(result)).not.toContain(\"password\");\n  });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Query Test Pattern: `get-command-center-attention.test.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, expect, it } from \"vitest\";\nimport type { Sql } from \"postgres\";\nimport {\n  COMMAND_CENTER_DEFAULTS,\n  getCommandCenterAttention,\n} from \"../get-command-center-attention\";\nimport type { PeekCommandCenterAttentionId } from \"../../../../lib/types/peek\";\n\ntype SqlCall = {\n  text: string;\n  values: ReadonlyArray<unknown>;\n};\n\ntype ResponseValue = ReadonlyArray<{ value: number | string }> | Error;\n\ntype SqlMock = {\n  sql: Sql;\n  calls: ReadonlyArray<SqlCall>;\n};\n\n// Build a SQL mock that returns a sequence of responses, one per call.\n// Each response is either a row array (success) or an Error (rejection).\nfunction createSqlMock(responses: ReadonlyArray<ResponseValue>): SqlMock {\n  const calls: SqlCall[] = [];\n  let cursor = 0;\n\n  const fn = (strings: TemplateStringsArray, ...values: unknown[]) => {\n    const text = [...strings].join(\"?\");\n    calls.push({ text, values: [...values] });\n    const next = responses[cursor++];\n    if (next instanceof Error) {\n      return Promise.reject(next);\n    }\n    return Promise.resolve(next ?? []);\n  };\n\n  // Cast through unknown — only the tagged-template surface is exercised here.\n  const sql = fn as unknown as Sql;\n  return { sql, calls };\n}\n\nconst ALL_IDS: ReadonlyArray<PeekCommandCenterAttentionId> = [\n  \"failed_claims\",\n  \"dead_queue_events\",\n  \"stuck_rounds_flipyou_potshot\",\n  \"stuck_rounds_closecall\",\n  \"pending_sol_crate_payouts\",\n  \"stale_active_dogpile_events\",\n  \"high_value_exports_24h\",\n];\n\ndescribe(\"getCommandCenterAttention\", () => {\n  it(\"populated: returns one PeekMetric per attention id with FR-4 bookkeeping\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock([\n      [{ value: 3 }],\n      [{ value: 1 }],\n      [{ value: 5 }],\n      [{ value: 2 }],\n      [{ value: 4 }],\n      [{ value: 6 }],\n      [{ value: 7 }],\n    ]);\n    const now = new Date(\"2026-04-25T10:00:00.000Z\");\n\n    const result = await getCommandCenterAttention({ sql: mock.sql, now });\n\n    expect(result.generatedAt).toBe(\"2026-04-25T10:00:00.000Z\");\n    expect(result.metrics).toHaveLength(7);\n    expect(result.metrics.map((m) => m.id)).toEqual(ALL_IDS);\n\n    for (const metric of result.metrics) {\n      expect(metric.asOf).toBe(\"2026-04-25T10:00:00.000Z\");\n      expect(metric.freshness).toBe(\"live\");\n      expect(metric.label.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n      expect(metric.definition.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n      expect(metric.source.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n      expect(metric.windowLabel.length).toBeGreaterThan(0);\n      expect(metric.drilldownHref).not.toBeNull();\n    }\n\n    const byId = new Map(result.metrics.map((m) => [m.id, m]));\n    expect(byId.get(\"failed_claims\")?.value).toBe(3);\n    expect(byId.get(\"failed_claims\")?.valueDisplay).toBe(\"3\");\n    expect(byId.get(\"failed_claims\")?.source).toBe(\"referral_claims\");\n    expect(byId.get(\"dead_queue_events\")?.value).toBe(1);\n    expect(byId.get(\"stuck_rounds_flipyou_potshot\")?.value).toBe(5);\n    expect(byId.get(\"stuck_rounds_closecall\")?.value).toBe(2);\n    expect(byId.get(\"pending_sol_crate_payouts\")?.value).toBe(4);\n    expect(byId.get(\"stale_active_dogpile_events\")?.value).toBe(6);\n    expect(byId.get(\"high_value_exports_24h\")?.value).toBe(7);\n    expect(byId.get(\"high_value_exports_24h\")?.source).toBe(\"operator_events\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"populated (large counts): formats valueDisplay with a thousands separator\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock([\n      [{ value: 1234 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n    ]);\n\n    const result = await getCommandCenterAttention({ sql: mock.sql });\n\n    const failed = result.metrics.find((m) => m.id === \"failed_claims\");\n    expect(failed?.value).toBe(1234);\n    expect(failed?.valueDisplay).toBe(\"1,234\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"populated (string count): coerces a postgres ::text count to a number\", async () => {\n    // postgres-js can return numeric counts as strings depending on driver\n    // configuration; the query module must coerce them back to numbers.\n    const mock = createSqlMock([\n      [{ value: \"12\" }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n      [{ value: 0 }],\n    ]);\n\n    const result = await getCommandCenterAttention({ sql: mock.sql });\n\n    const failed = result.metrics.find((m) => m.id === \"failed_claims\");\n    expect(failed?.value).toBe(12);\n    expect(failed?.valueDisplay).toBe(\"12\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"sparse: every empty row coerces to a zero count without dropping the metric\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock([[], [], [], [], [], [], []]);\n\n    const result = await getCommandCenterAttention({ sql: mock.sql });\n\n    expect(result.metrics).toHaveLength(7);\n    for (const metric of result.metrics) {\n      expect(metric.value).toBe(0);\n      expect(metric.valueDisplay).toBe(\"0\");\n    }\n  });\n\n  it(\"threshold overrides: surface in the windowLabel and definition copy\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock([[], [], [], [], [], [], []]);\n\n    const result = await getCommandCenterAttention({\n      sql: mock.sql,\n      thresholds: {\n        stuckRoundsAgeMinutes: 10,\n        stuckRoundsMaxSettleAttempts: 6,\n        stuckCloseCallAgeMinutes: 7,\n        exportWindowHours: 12,\n        exportRowCountThreshold: 250,\n      },\n    });\n\n    const stuck = result.metrics.find(\n      (m) => m.id === \"stuck_rounds_flipyou_potshot\",\n    );\n    expect(stuck?.windowLabel).toContain(\"10m\");\n    expect(stuck?.windowLabel).toContain(\"> 6\");\n\n    const cc = result.metrics.find((m) => m.id === \"stuck_rounds_closecall\");\n    expect(cc?.windowLabel).toContain(\"7m\");\n\n    const exports = result.metrics.find((m) => m.id === \"high_value_exports_24h\");\n    expect(exports?.windowLabel).toContain(\"Last 12h\");\n    expect(exports?.definition).toContain(\"12h\");\n    expect(exports?.definition).toContain(\"250\");\n  });\n\n  it(\"default thresholds: match the published COMMAND_CENTER_DEFAULTS\", async () => {\n    const mock = createSqlMock([[], [], [], [], [], [], []]);\n\n    const result = await getCommandCenterAttention({ sql: mock.sql });\n\n    const stuck = result.metrics.find(\n      (m) => m.id === \"stuck_rounds_flipyou_potshot\",\n    );\n    expect(stuck?.windowLabel).toContain(\n      `${COMMAND_CENTER_DEFAULTS.stuckRoundsAgeMinutes}m`,\n    );\n    expect(stuck?.windowLabel).toContain(\n      `> ${COMMAND_CENTER_DEFAULTS.stuckRoundsMaxSettleAttempts}`,\n    );\n\n    const exports = result.metrics.find((m) => m.id === \"high_value_exports_24h\");\n    expect(exports?.windowLabel).toContain(\n      `Last ${COMMAND_CENTER_DEFAULTS.exportWindowHours}h`,\n    );\n  });\n\n  it(\"load-er